other_tests.findings: The liver is normal in echotexture without discrete mass or lesion. No intrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. The gallbladder is distended with an increased gallbladder wall thickness, measuring 6 mm. Multiple gallstones are identified. Pericholecystic fluid noted. The common bile duct is not dilated measuring 5 mm. No pancreatic duct dilatation evident. No free fluid identified.
